Sliding Window

Algorithm
Create an array occ[26] to store the frequency of each uppercase character in the current window.
Set:
left = 0
maxOcc = 0
ans = 0
Move right from 0 to the end of the string.
For every right, add s.charAt(right) to the frequency array.
Update maxOcc, which stores the highest frequency of a single character in the current window.
Calculate how many characters need replacement:



class Solution {
    public int characterReplacement(String s, int k) {

        int left = 0,  right =0;
        int[] occ = new int[26];

        int maxOcc = 0;
        int ans =0;

        for(right =0 ; right < s.length(); right++)
        {
            maxOcc = Math.max(maxOcc , ++occ[s.charAt(right) - 'A']);

            if( right - left + 1 - maxOcc > k)
            {
                occ[s.charAt(left) - 'A']--;
                left++;
            }

            ans = Math.max(ans, right-left+1);

        }
        

        return ans;
    }
}
